$ SQL Developer: Tools -> Preferences -> Database -> Third Party JDBC Drivers

The menu *Tools -> Preferences -> Database -> Third Party JDBC Drivers* allows to specify the location of JDBC drivers so that
→ development/Software/Oracle-SQL-Developer[SQL Developer] can be used to connect to non-→ development/databases/Oracle databases.

A description how it is possible to connect to → development/databases/SQL-Server is → development/Software/Oracle-SQL-Developer/connect-to-SQL-Server[here] and one
that shows how to connect to → development/databases/MySQL is → development/Software/Oracle-SQL-Developer/connect-to-MySQL[here].
